ies of him, almost no full-fledged intellectual biography of him exists in any language. This study of the years before his momentous move to Jaffa in 1904, drawing on little-known works, including recently published manuscripts, begins to fill that gap. It traces his life and times in the remarkably intense Rabbinic intellectual milieu of late nineteenth-century Eastern Europe, and his path from a profound, regularly rationalist traditionalism, towards a dynamic theology and spiritual practice weaving together Kabbalah, philosophy, universal ethics, and romantic mysticism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aJewish philosophy. 0aRabbiszEurope, EasternvBiography. 0aReligious ZionismxPhilosophy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Jewish Studies.2bisacsh  aAvraham Yitzhaq Ha-Cohen Kook.  aChief Rabbinate.  aKabbalah.  aModern Jewish history and thought.  aRav Kook.  aReligious Zionism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074321008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618119544zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618119544423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781618119544/original  a978-3-11-074321-0  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Packa